Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}.

Squeeze the lime juice into a #medium bowl{} and add the @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then add 3/4 of the @mayonnaise{64} and mix together. Add the @coleslaw mix{120} and mix again. Set aside.

Halve the @glazed burger bun{2}.

Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop the wedges onto a #large baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, sprinkle over the @black sesame seeds{5}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Drain the @halloumi{125} then cut it into 2 slices per person.

Put the @cornflour{10} into a #bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Cut each @British chicken thighs{3} into 2-3 pieces (depending on size), then add to the bowl of cornflour and toss to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{to drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the halloumi and fry until golden, turning frequently, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix together the @sriracha sauce{15}, @honey{15}, lime zest and @water{50}(for the sauce). Set the hot honey glaze aside.

Once the halloumi is cooked, transfer to a #plate{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

Put your frying pan back on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken in the pan. Fry until browned on each side and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 mins.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, add the honey mixture to the pan. Turn down the heat to medium and simmer until sticky, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove the pan from the heat and turn the chicken to coat it in the mixture.

When the wedges are almost cooked, put the burger buns into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Spread the remaining mayo on the base and top of each bun. Top with your chicken and any remaining hot honey sauce in the pan. Finish with the halloumi and bun lid.

Serve your craft burgers with the sesame wedges and slaw alongside. Enjoy!